{
  "texts": [
    "As demonstrated here, language models can simulate personas, including their cognitive imperfections.",
    "This has implications for achieving cognitive abilities through LLMs that surpass human capabilities.",
    "Even if an LLM encompasses a more comprehensive world model than any human, prompting it to simulate a human or human-like expert would not result in super-human behavior, since the human imperfections would be simulated as well.",
    "PLOS ONE | https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0298522March 13, 2024"
  ]
}